{{画像提供依頼|date=2024th year 4月|cat=中津市|祭礼}} '''Nakatsu Gion''' (中津祇園, なかつぎおん) is a festival held in {{ill|Oita Prefecture|ja|大分県|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|Nakatsu City|ja|中津市|12=draft|12=draft}}. It features processions of portable shrines ({{ill|Portable Shrine|ja|神輿|12=draft|12=draft}}) and festival floats ({{ill|Festival Float|ja|山車|12=draft|12=draft}}).
== Characteristics == It is a festival with a tradition of roughly over 580 years, representing Nakatsu, a castle town of 100,000 koku. It is counted as one of the "Top Three Festivals of Buzen" ({{ill|Usa Hachiman Shrine Summer Crossing Festival|ja|宇佐八幡宮 夏越し祭|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|Ogura Gion Festival|ja|小倉祇園祭|12=draft|12=draft}}), one of the "Top Three Gion Festivals of Buzen" ({{ill|Ogura Gion Drum|ja|小倉祇園太鼓|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|Imai Gion|ja|今井祇園|12=draft|12=draft}}), and one of the "Three Major Gion Festivals of Oita" ({{ill|Hita Gion Festival|ja|日田祇園祭|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|Usuki Gion Festival|ja|臼杵祇園まつり|12=draft|12=draft}}).<ref>[http://www.oitabank.co.jp/hometown/kawara/kawara-article/150810-1.html {{ill|Nakatsu Gion|ja|中津祇園|12=draft|12=draft}}] Oita Bank, August 10, 2015</ref><ref>{{PDFlink|[http://www.hues.kyushu-u.ac.jp/education/student/pdf/2010/2HE09033W.pdf Memory and Practice Concerning the Imai Gion Festival]}}</ref><ref>[http://www.oitabank.co.jp/hometown/kawara/kawara-article/140804-2.html {{ill|Nakatsu Gion|ja|中津祇園|12=draft|12=draft}}] Oita Bank, August 4, 2014</ref>
It derives from the tradition of the Gion Festival of {{ill|Yasaka Shrine|ja|八坂神社|12=draft|12=draft}} in Kyoto. It consists of two distinct Gion festivals: the "Upper Gion" centered on {{ill|Nakatsu Shrine|ja|中津大神宮|lt=Nakatsu Shrine|lt_ja=中津神社|12=draft|12=draft}}, and the "Lower Gion" centered on Yasaka Shrine of the subsidiary shrine of {{ill|Kuranishihama Shrine|ja|闇無浜神社|12=draft|12=draft}}.<ref name="double">[http://nakatsu-gion.sakura.ne.jp/wp/midokoro/double/ Two “Gion Festivals”] Nakatsu Gion Preservation Council</ref>
== Characteristics == == History ==
