== Characteristics == It is a festival with a tradition of roughly over 580 years, representing Nakatsu, a castle town of 100,000 koku. It is counted as one of the "Top Three Festivals of Buzen" ({{ill|Usa Hachiman Shrine Summer Crossing Festival|ja|宇佐八幡宮 夏越し祭|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Usa Hachiman Shrine Summer Crossing Festival|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} and {{ill|Ogura Gion Festival|ja|小倉祇園祭|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ogura Gion Festival|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}), one of the "Top Three Gion Festivals of Buzen" ({{ill|Ogura Gion Drum|ja|小倉祇園太鼓|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ogura Gion Drum|qq=}} and {{ill|Imai Gion|ja|今井祇園|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Imai Gion|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}), and one of the "Three Major Gion Festivals of Oita" ({{ill|Hita Gion Festival|ja|日田祇園祭|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hita Gion Festival|qq=}} and {{ill|Usuki Gion Festival|ja|臼杵祇園まつり|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Usuki Gion Festival|qq=}}).<ref>[http://www.oitabank.co.jp/hometown/kawara/kawara-article/150810-1.html {{ill|Nakatsu Gion|ja|中津祇園|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nakatsu Gion|qq=}}] Oita Bank, August 10, 2015</ref><ref>{{PDFlink|[http://www.hues.kyushu-u.ac.jp/education/student/pdf/2010/2HE09033W.pdf Memory and Practice Concerning the Imai Gion Festival]}}</ref><ref>[http://www.oitabank.co.jp/hometown/kawara/kawara-article/140804-2.html {{ill|Nakatsu Gion|ja|中津祇園|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nakatsu Gion|qq=}}] Oita Bank, August 4, 2014</ref>
It derives from the tradition of the Gion Festival of [[:en:Yasaka Shrine|Yasaka Shrine]] in Kyoto. It consists of two distinct Gion festivals: the "Upper Gion" centered on {{ill|Nakatsu Shrine|ja|中津大神宮|lt=Nakatsu Shrine|lt_ja=中津神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nakatsu Shrine|qq=}}, and the "Lower Gion" centered on Yasaka Shrine of the subsidiary shrine of {{ill|Kuranishihama Shrine|ja|闇無浜神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kuranishihama Shrine|qq=}}.<ref name="double">[http://nakatsu-gion.sakura.ne.jp/wp/midokoro/double/ Two “Gion Festivals”] Nakatsu Gion Preservation Council</ref>
